JOHANNESBURG - A South African woman working in Mauritius was found murdered in her home on Monday.Lara Rijs (32), who worked for the Geneva Management Group, was found on her bed with stab wounds. Reports suggest her flat in Grand Bay is in a secure complex.A 55-year-old man was reportedly arrested in connection with the murder and is due to appear in court on Tuesday. The motive for the murder is not known. Everyone at the Geneva Management Group is distraught and deeply saddened by the news of Lara Rijs death," said Geneva Management Group CEO Dave Elzas."We extend our most sincere condolences to her family and will make every assistance available to them at this difficult time. eNCA